javadoc.text: * Interface for all 64 bit floating point rectangular matrices.
javadoc.author: Peter Abeles

javadoc.text: * Returns the value of value of the specified matrix element.

* Same as {@link #get} but does not perform bounds check on input parameters. This results in about a 25% * speed increase but potentially sacrifices stability and makes it more difficult to track down simple errors. * It is not recommended that this function be used, except in highly optimized code where the bounds are * implicitly being checked.
* Sets the value of the specified matrix element.

* Same as {@link #set} but does not perform bounds check on input parameters. This results in about a 25% * speed increase but potentially sacrifices stability and makes it more difficult to track down simple errors. * It is not recommended that this function be used, except in highly optimized code where the bounds are * implicitly being checked.
* Returns the number of rows in this matrix.
* Returns the number of columns in this matrix.
* Returns the number of elements in this matrix, which is the number of rows * times the number of columns.
javadoc.return: Number of elements in this matrix.
